OL,3,CFerry worker jailed for 20 months
OL,4,Cfollowing fatal boat collision
OL,6,FThe charge related to the collision of
OL,7,Fthe Condor Commodore Goodwill Ferry
OL,8,Fand L'Ecume II on 9 December 2022,
OL,9,Fwhich resulted in the deaths of three
OL,10,Ffishermen aboard L'Ecume.
OL,12,FCarr was assigned to the bridge
OL,13,Falongside Artur Sevash-Zade, a
OL,14,FUkrainian national, who was formally
OL,15,Fdischarged of endangering lives.
OL,17,FIn handing out his sentence, presiding
OL,18,Fjudge Sir John Saunders said that
OL,19,Fwhile Carr did not deliberately crash
OL,20,Finto L'Ecume II, he had "ample
OL,21,Fopportunity" to avoid it.
