OL,6,F"The sentence we pass has to take into
OL,7,Faccount the pain this has caused," he
OL,8,Fruled.
OL,10,F"Whatever fault there may have been
OL,11,Ffrom L'Ecume II, when it became
OL,12,Fapparent they weren't altering course,
OL,13,FCarr should have given way.
OL,15,F"He didn't deliberately cause the
OL,16,Fcollision. He failed to devote all his
OL,17,Fattention to avoiding the collision;
OL,18,Fhe divided his attention."
