OL,6,FCarr's lawyer, Simon Thomas, read out
OL,7,Fa letter of remorse from the ferry
OL,8,Fworker.
OL,10,F"I recognise the pain and anger felt
OL,11,Fby family and friends," it read. "I'm
OL,12,Ftruly sorry for their loss and the
OL,13,Fevents that led to it. I take full
OL,14,Fresponsibility for my part in this
OL,15,Ftragedy."
OL,17,FCarr was originally charged alongside
OL,18,FMr Sevash-Zade, another crewmember on
OL,19,Fboard the Commodore Goodwill.
